fields.description:
The apache module that looks at the Subversion authentication file doesn't support the wildcard syntax.  For example, this configuration should allow anyone, including anonymous, to read the directory:

{noformat}
[/PL]
* = r
{noformat}

If Crowd admin is connecting to LDAP server over the internet (especially via VPN) and importing a large number of users, this can result in the following error:

{noformat}
ERROR [crowd.console.interceptor.XWorkTransactionInterceptor] Invoking rollback for transaction on action '/console/secure/dataimport/directoryconfirmation.action (DirectoryConfirmation.execute())' due to throwable: java.lang.IllegalStateException: getAttribute: Session already invalidated
{noformat}
